    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but my doctor literally told me that consistent levels are the most important thing for hypertension. if i only take 20mg now, my blood pressure is gonna be low all day until my next dose, right? it seems way more logical to just take the 40mg to compensate and stay in that therapeutic range so i dont have a stroke or something. can't you just confirm that taking the double dose is the standard way to handle a missed dose to keep the levels steady?",
